Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.58,0:00:07.52,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Let's get started with another Wednesday Downtown. Welcome everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.42,0:00:07.52,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:08.67,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.67,0:00:11.77,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Everyone please welcome our first presenter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:22.20,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Yasuko Mitsuura from Oasis
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.08,0:00:26.12,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You're usually over there
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.08,0:00:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is my first time on this side
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.12,0:00:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, thank you for having me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.49,0:00:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Today it's just, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.16,0:00:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have to dig into this?\NIt's bound to bring out the worst in women.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.01,0:00:35.75,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Really. It really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.38,0:00:39.08,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You're really pushing it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.08,0:00:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The theory I've brought is this-
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.75,0:00:46.29,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Theory: If a profile picture has two girls \Nit belongs to the cute one
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.68,0:00:48.02,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,That's harsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.60,0:00:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's heartless~
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.34,0:00:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that might be possible
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.68,0:00:59.82,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Talents can be really bad
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.95,0:00:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, talents and models-
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.82,0:01:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,don't seem to be as bad about it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.41,0:01:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But just look at what they put in their blog posts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.80,0:01:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They ask me for a picture to post saying "I worked with Mitsuura-san!"\NSo they take it-
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.20,0:01:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they upload it.\NWhen I go to check it, I'm shocked!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.49,0:01:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They look absolutely stunning while I stand there with my eyes half-shut
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.77,0:01:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What is with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.43,0:01:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like she was thinking "Well as long as I look good".\NIt's scary, truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.45,0:01:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.04,0:01:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a lot of my friends are similar.\NThey ask for a picture but-
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.08,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They only look at themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.18,0:01:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.04,0:01:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's best that if you ask for a photo,\Nyou should let them take it for you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.32,0:01:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is something only {\i1}moderately{\i0} cute girls do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.33,0:01:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Real cute girls have real cute friends
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.75,0:01:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That fastball came out of nowhere-\N right into my face
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.23,0:01:55.34,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,KERPOW, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.34,0:01:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm speechless
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.44,0:01:59.86,Hamada,,0,0,0,,That's quite an opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.86,0:02:02.61,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,She just went over your theory with her own
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:09.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Coming up-\NDoes the profile picture belong to the cuter girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.28,0:02:10.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After that-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.16,0:02:14.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Can you bunt a home run?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.69,0:02:16.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We put it to the test...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.94,0:02:19.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...using 300 km/h balls from a pitching machine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.08,0:02:24.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then, can you play telephone game with various genres?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.74,0:02:31.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The theory that you are not considered a professional unless you have a perfect knowledge about your signature act
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:53.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We're investigating the theory that if a profile picture has two girls-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.97,0:03:02.01,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I wonder if this will end up being true?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.85,0:02:57.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it belongs to the cute one
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:03:03.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,First, we searched for girls that have a profile picture with their friend in it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:08.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then we asked nearby boys which is cuter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:12.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Finally we'll find out which one is the real owner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.24,0:03:15.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Will it be the cute one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.99,0:03:19.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This was the first photo we found
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:24.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A profile picture with friends, ages 25 and 22
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.89,0:03:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please tell us which of the girls in this photo is cuter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.83,0:03:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The one on the left is cutest
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.98,0:03:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The left one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.42,0:03:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.56,0:03:41.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With 3 votes to 0, the streets have chosen the girl on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.73,0:03:45.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,So which one does the profile picture belong to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.17,0:03:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for helping
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:51.72,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,They got her to come out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:52.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What will it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:04:01.19,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Ah, of course it is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.85,0:04:00.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was the cute one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.59,0:04:07.38,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't say that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:05.17,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,She's cuter in the picture
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you use a pair photo here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.82,0:04:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To show off my looks
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.92,0:04:12.85,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's her best angle right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, it's a pretty good photo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.31,0:04:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But it didn't look very glamorous with me alone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.84,0:04:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And photo alone doesn't look as cheerful so
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.84,0:04:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm in it with a friend"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.00,0:04:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"I look pretty"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.66,0:04:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Those 2 things are-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what I consider
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when I decide
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.20,0:04:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, which of you is more popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she's younger so she gets more attention
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.16,0:04:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.62,0:04:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's embarrassing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.64,0:04:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pathetic
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.14,0:04:43.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She insists she didn't use her friend as a fashion accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Around how many guys have asked you out, total?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.41,0:04:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been counting, really
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.92,0:04:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a rough estimate?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.76,0:04:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to be exact.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.51,0:04:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably around 40 or 50
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.01,0:05:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:02.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Moving on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.80,0:05:04.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This pair photo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.94,0:05:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the one on the right is cuter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.02,0:05:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I also prefer the girl on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I also think the girl in center frame is cute
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.22,0:05:16.08,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is just bad
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.22,0:05:16.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The judgment on the streets is "right"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:18.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Sure enough
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.33,0:05:22.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They're correct after all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.04,0:05:25.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This one was also the cuter girl
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,With this there's a sense that \N"Oh, they're such good friends!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But a selfie kind of screams-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.05,0:05:34.12,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,So, good friends
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.64,0:05:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm obsessed with myself"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:39.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Next
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.18,0:05:41.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,These two
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.62,0:05:46.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I'll go with the left one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.42,0:05:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I also think the left is cuter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.57,0:05:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I also say left
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:53.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The decision is the girl on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:56.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but usually the profile picture should belong-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.23,0:06:00.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to the person in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:02.02,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It could be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.76,0:06:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:06.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Of course
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.99,0:06:10.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's the girl on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.56,0:06:12.34,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,That's freaky~
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:17.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although the rate of cute girls using pictures is high,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.24,0:06:22.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,most of the pair photos we found didn't have much difference in cuteness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.81,0:06:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think many women-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.47,0:06:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,use pair photos with someone much less attractive?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:36.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It somehow exudes the sense that she is obviously cuter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.22,0:06:37.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then, there's-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.86,0:06:40.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This pair photo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.61,0:06:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please pick the cuter girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh okay
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The right one, yo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.71,0:06:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The one in white, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.01,0:06:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.35,0:06:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The one in white?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The left one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.09,0:06:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Left?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.98,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the purikura effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the girl on the right is going to look worse
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:07.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is the first time the decision has split 2-1
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.76,0:07:11.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,So which one is the owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.28,0:07:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there she is. She's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.47,0:07:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello\NHello
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.36,0:07:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, we're from Wednesday Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.08,0:07:26.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.61,0:07:34.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We're not sure which girl this is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.98,0:07:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.83,0:07:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In the purikura machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.26,0:07:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...I pick the cutest one...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,from those that we took
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.81,0:07:53.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Somehow, the purikura created this totally distorted picture of the girl on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:55.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At this point
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.08,0:07:57.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It seems less about cuteness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:08:00.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And more about the effects used
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:04.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Our next photo is this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.34,0:08:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the left is cuter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.09,0:08:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The left one
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:13.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,By some stroke of fate we ran into this man
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, excuse me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't you been on TV before?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.34,0:08:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.03,0:08:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.60,0:08:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.12,0:08:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're shooting Wednesday Downtown now
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:28.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's right, this man is-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.42,0:08:31.90,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Back from spring
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.24,0:08:35.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the one we met when we were looking for fish-faces\NThe hippo-face man
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do for a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Construction worker
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Construction?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.84,0:08:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.75,0:08:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was scouted by a comedy agent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now I'm, uh, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing extra work in comedy productions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.23,0:08:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for helping with that theory
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:08:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, no trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.31,0:08:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.88,0:08:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have the day off
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I go back to work tomorrow night
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.41,0:09:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting in my room all day would be boring
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.61,0:09:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to Shibuya?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.17,0:09:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I spend a lot of time in Shibuya when I have a break
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Have there been any consequences?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.20,0:09:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,People greet me a lot\NIf I go to Ikebukoro-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.75,0:09:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,People will even come up-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.54,0:09:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask to take a photo with me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.14,0:09:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:27.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We ask him, one of our many friends, who is cuter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The left one, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.90,0:09:34.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, this photo belongs to the girl on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.70,0:09:38.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And this is what the girl on the left looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:45.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The purikura effect completely changed them both
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.25,0:09:49.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And our final photo
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.03,0:09:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The right one
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.29,0:09:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The blond? Interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.90,0:09:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Left
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.97,0:09:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Left
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:10:00.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The decision of the street is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.72,0:10:02.63,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.19,0:10:02.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...the woman on the left 2vs1 however...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.92,0:10:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, hello
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.36,0:10:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come over here
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.58,0:10:15.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The result is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.57,0:10:21.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Based on the colour of the hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:27.54,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I get why she took it from a high angle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:25.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...it seems that she is the one on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.60,0:10:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you use a pair shot for your icon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.48,0:10:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When you take selfies, I end up touching it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.45,0:10:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...using filters and such
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.28,0:10:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But I get the "You look nothing like that" response a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.42,0:10:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"You look nothing like that"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.52,0:10:43.03,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.03,0:10:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.15,0:10:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...I get told "That's fraud!" a lot as well
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.97,0:10:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's fraud"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:55.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With that, the cute one is the user of the photo but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:10:57.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...profile pictures and reality don't match up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing, you can't just trust the photos...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,...that's the only thing we get from this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.65,0:11:06.20,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It's incredible...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.20,0:11:08.50,Hamada,,0,0,0,,...it makes that much of a difference
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.50,0:11:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be good to be like "No purikura!"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.55,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, if you just use purikura, from a male perspective...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...they all look cute but if you open the lid...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't she end up alone if she continues like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.40,0:11:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be hard for her to find someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.36,0:11:28.48,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I think that's saying too much
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:34.01,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Since we had good girls that accepted to do the interview right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes yes, they were open about it so...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:39.66,Hamada,,0,0,0,,But didn't you just think "that's a completely different person"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.66,0:11:44.33,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,But, I really thought that her heart was beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.33,0:11:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.71,0:11:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He said so many thing while watching the video though
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.86,0:11:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones that accepted to go on tv were all lovely people, personality wise
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.45,0:11:54.71,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Right the ones that did yes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.71,0:11:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like, uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.16,0:12:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...we're in an age where small jokes like that wouldn't make them super angry
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.31,0:12:07.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Next we have the corner where we present and investigate theories from around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.64,0:12:10.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Viewers' Theory Corner
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:14.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Tonight's presenter is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.32,0:12:16.95,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It's Tamura Kenji!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.95,0:12:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for having me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.18,0:12:23.33,Hamada,,0,0,0,,The hell is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.87,0:12:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hair is crazy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.63,0:12:25.70,Hamada,,0,0,0,,No I mean it's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.70,0:12:27.90,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Did you get a perm or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a perm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.64,0:12:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...and I ended up leaving it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...and it was pretty funny
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.47,0:12:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We were like "We did it!" with the make-up artist...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"We got a good one"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.16,0:12:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...and I came in like this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.35,0:12:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't that funny afterall was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.54,0:12:48.90,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,No it wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.03,0:12:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.90,0:12:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on. Here is the first theory!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.47,0:12:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Theory: You can play the Telephone Game with puppets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.05,0:13:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.43,0:13:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You might think to yourself "Hmm?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.89,0:13:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The Telephone Game is where you say something to the next person's ear and it goes around...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.14,0:13:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,...however, not using any speech...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.78,0:13:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...we got professionals of expression together...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,...and we made them play the Telephone Game. That's the theory
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:18.16,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You mean like drawings and stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.16,0:13:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.52,0:13:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we have a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.33,0:13:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got the puppeteer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.83,0:13:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And a portrait artist
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Latte Artist
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.27,0:13:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that it'll definitely stop at the latte artist
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.20,0:13:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Can they even make anything more than a panda?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.39,0:13:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's the condescension!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.24,0:13:38.33,Hamada,,0,0,0,,That's not ok
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.67,0:13:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's no good
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll piss people off for sure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.03,0:13:42.98,Hamada,,0,0,0,,"Nothing more than a panda?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We're experienced in that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.98,0:13:44.22,Hamada,,0,0,0,,We are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.22,0:13:47.17,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,How did you experience it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.22,0:13:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The cymbal theory, cymbal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.17,0:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People were really pissed off at me for making fun of the cymbal guy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.48,0:13:53.16,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.16,0:13:57.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We're investigating the theory that you can play the Telephone Game with puppets
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.52,0:14:00.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With that, this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.20,0:14:04.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,we will have these six pros from different genres, including the puppeteer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.85,0:14:09.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,communicate an idea using just their proficiencies
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.64,0:14:12.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If the theme that was given by Announcer Kuniyama
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.05,0:14:15.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,manages to go through to Announcer Yoshida at the end
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.23,0:14:19.29,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh the first one is drawing as expected
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.23,0:14:18.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,we will have proven the theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.88,0:14:22.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The theme is this
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.28,0:14:25.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Antonio Inoki hitting a homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.11,0:14:28.22,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,This is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.22,0:14:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.09,0:14:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.69,0:14:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With that, please get started on your craft
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.71,0:14:39.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At first, we start with the portrait artist
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.95,0:14:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it usually take for you to draw one picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.43,0:14:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, if it's just the face, I draw in a bout 10 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.40,0:14:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,About 10 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.35,0:14:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you confident in yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uuhmm, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.32,0:14:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...I want them to at least understand the person, since it's a portrait
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.09,0:14:58.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minutes since the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.74,0:15:03.01,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is really important
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.65,0:15:01.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The end result is here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.48,0:15:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.83,0:15:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the important points exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The points are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.69,0:15:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd have to understand that it's "this person"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.41,0:15:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the red scarf
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you can see his satisfaction with the homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.11,0:15:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.83,0:15:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah you can see the point being given too
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.20,0:15:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I kind of tried to squeeze it all in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:31.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And when she shows it to the pantomime...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:34.08,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be okay with a pantomime?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.17,0:15:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you understand what it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.39,0:15:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I did
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.72,0:15:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhm, Mr. Inoki is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.00,0:15:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...in a game of baseball...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.87,0:15:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,...hitting a homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.91,0:15:51.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With that, the Telephone Pantomime begins
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:16:00.30,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's not that funny
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:05.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't he get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.21,0:16:09.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She brings up the characteristic chin with her hand movements...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.00,0:16:12.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...1, 2, 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:14.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...Da! movement...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:18.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...to relay that it's Inoki
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.10,0:16:20.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.44,0:16:32.77,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,She's pretty good
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.47,0:16:35.81,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,She brings the pose again huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.88,0:16:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.91,0:16:41.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Next is latte art
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.95,0:16:41.87,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is where we might have problems
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.28,0:16:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you exactly doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.58,0:16:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm first building the silhouette...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.27,0:16:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...with that the contour?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.42,0:16:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, this is chocolate sauce, to draw on the details
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.47,0:16:58.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,15 minutes passed working on their craft
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:17:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.47,0:17:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the scene of Antonio Inoki hitting a homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.86,0:17:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you divide it to two cups?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you draw things too small...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:16.25,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh my god, I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.63,0:17:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...the portrait would end up unrecognizable, since the canvas is so small
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,...so I thought about increasing the canvases
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.92,0:17:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the chin is very characteristic...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.40,0:17:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...and also his red towel. I wanted to show that it's Antonio Inoki...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.16,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...to make them understand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.77,0:17:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And drawing the ball flying away...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.27,0:17:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...on my second cup
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.52,0:17:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping that this is understandable by the next person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.31,0:17:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.08,0:17:46.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The puppeteer, seeing this work of art...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.53,0:17:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Antonio Inoki is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,...playing baseball
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.83,0:17:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your answer correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.01,0:17:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.63,0:17:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what you understood
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:17:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.02,0:18:06.56,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This could comeback somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.93,0:18:05.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The homerun aspect of the question was lost at this point
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.34,0:18:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Please start explaining the theme to the next person
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.63,0:18:35.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Here also, we get the hand movements to show the chin...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:39.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...trying to do the "Da!" but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.35,0:18:40.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,1
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:41.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,2
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:43.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Da!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.69,0:18:48.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She forgot the "3"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:50.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.86,0:18:59.92,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Is it a bit tough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.55,0:19:04.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's like a bunt
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.64,0:19:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.85,0:19:10.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What did the fifth person get from the puppet's movements
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.52,0:19:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please show it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It ended up like this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.67,0:19:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A batter looking to hit
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.08,0:19:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a very fast ball
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.57,0:19:27.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With the puppet, we completely lost Inoki
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.74,0:19:32.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But by some miracle, the homerun idea came back
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:36.42,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Let's make another miracle and get Inoki back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.97,0:19:37.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The balloon artist seeing this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.18,0:19:41.73,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Would he've been able to make Inoki with balloons anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.92,0:19:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a clear image in your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be thinking about it while making it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:54.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After 20 minutes of hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.30,0:19:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm done
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:19:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to convey?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.84,0:20:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A batter trying to hit a fastball
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:05.05,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,This is amazing though...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.05,0:20:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically I wanted to depict the motion of a fast thrown ball
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.35,0:20:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,by creating this spiral thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The face looks a bit like Downtown's Matsumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.43,0:20:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is just something I did for fun...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.96,0:20:17.49,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's true they look alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:21.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For the sake of fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.67,0:20:25.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Matsumoto element appeared into the sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.10,0:20:24.80,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yeah but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.80,0:20:28.01,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He thought too much about the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:28.01,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He really did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:26.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As a result...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,, Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.94,0:20:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Balloons right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.08,0:20:37.51,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yoshida should get it at once....
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.51,0:20:38.85,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.32,0:20:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.32,0:20:42.32,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The ring shoes and the pants are definitely saying Inoki!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:43.89,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Is it so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.02,0:20:43.89,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.45,0:20:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Announcer Yoshida, please tell us your answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.29,0:20:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A blond
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,baseball player
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.96,0:20:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,hits
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a flying ball
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with a bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.50,0:21:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, this is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:05.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And with that, the elements "Inoki" and "homerun" disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.91,0:21:04.28,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It would end up like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.11,0:21:09.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the element of Matsumoto also wasn't mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.88,0:21:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is embarrassing isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.25,0:21:14.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, a second try after some changes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.32,0:21:16.89,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It definitely can be done
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.89,0:21:18.56,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,They should change the order
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.03,0:21:22.96,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yeah right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:25.23,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The marionette is the point here...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.89,0:21:22.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This time they discussed an approach that should result in success.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.23,0:21:24.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the outcome...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.70,0:21:28.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The first half consists of the illustrating artists,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.53,0:21:28.43,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,, Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.43,0:21:32.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,, and the more difficult genres are put towards the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.24,0:21:35.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so the second phrase is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.47,0:21:36.27,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Tricky!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.27,0:21:38.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A gorilla that failed the exams.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.99,0:21:57.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The second phrase is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.90,0:21:58.90,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's tricky!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.33,0:22:01.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A gorilla that failed the exams.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.03,0:22:02.10,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The phrase...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.10,0:22:03.97,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,They don't even take exams
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.97,0:22:05.04,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Cute...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.93,0:22:04.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,First, what the portrait artist created...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.84,0:22:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the large gorilla realizing...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.94,0:22:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the exam part is shown through the sakura
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.77,0:22:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but since it's a fail the sakura petals have fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.54,0:22:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But this wouldn't be enough to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.38,0:22:15.28,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is difficult!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.61,0:22:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so I show that his exam number is missing from the pass list.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.25,0:22:21.02,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.15,0:22:23.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The latte artist who sees this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.09,0:22:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A gorilla that failed the exams.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.29,0:22:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,100 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.66,0:22:31.60,Hamada,,0,0,0,,This one's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.46,0:22:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah he is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.60,0:22:36.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,, And so, this illustration is recreated with latte art.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.13,0:22:36.90,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is amazing!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.90,0:22:39.27,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The latte artist is definitely underrated...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.27,0:22:41.64,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yeah we were making fun of him
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.37,0:22:40.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the collage artist that saw this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.57,0:22:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing sevens (card game)...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.21,0:22:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,monkey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.81,0:22:47.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A missed interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.04,0:22:47.41,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Why??
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.41,0:22:48.71,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Why sevens??
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.35,0:22:50.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And by creating that collage...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.28,0:22:50.95,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,What is he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.08,0:22:52.75,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He missed clues like the sakura petals...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.48,0:22:54.45,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The sakura...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.48,0:22:54.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Next, the balloon artist...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.52,0:22:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a monkey playing card games
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.79,0:23:01.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He got this correct, however
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.89,0:22:59.62,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,So it turned into a monkey...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.62,0:23:00.99,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,But he made it very well
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.29,0:23:02.89,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's great, though
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.29,0:23:02.89,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yeah, indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.19,0:23:05.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The pantomime who saw this...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.06,0:23:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A gorilla that plays sevens
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.23,0:23:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The point where he finds seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.54,0:23:15.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Somehow, "gorilla" comes back into the sequence...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.51,0:23:16.41,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The gorilla part is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.64,0:23:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A gorilla playing cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.08,0:23:23.41,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Gorilla was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.41,0:23:24.98,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,But this as gorilla...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.78,0:23:30.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Equally far from both a gorilla and playing cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.45,0:23:35.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the japanese style marionette is struggling fruitlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.59,0:23:36.56,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,How will that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.93,0:23:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A gorilla....
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.26,0:23:39.33,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is on point!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.63,0:23:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sits down after an act of intimidation...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.20,0:23:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and eats...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.30,0:23:44.97,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.80,0:23:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a banana.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.07,0:23:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, it's a miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.20,0:23:49.97,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's the paper guy's fault
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.17,0:23:52.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so the conclusion is, the telephone game is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.14,0:23:53.58,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Well yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.48,0:23:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was pretty close right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.48,0:23:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.81,0:23:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But the latte artist was great right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.58,0:23:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He was!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.65,0:24:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He was amazing right...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.62,0:24:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...Kawakita-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.99,0:24:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I sincerely apologise.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.22,0:24:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't ya going to Harajuku?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.72,0:24:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.92,0:24:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It really was,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.86,0:24:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and even more it being in colour.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.39,0:24:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.33,0:24:14.77,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,However, I didn't hear anything about using two cups...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.23,0:24:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you upset because there was no reaction to that guy making your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.30,0:24:21.54,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It's not that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.54,0:24:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's move on to the next theory! The theory is as follows:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.61,0:24:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The theory that one should have a perfect knowledge of their signature act or are not considered a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.12,0:24:36.09,Hamada,,0,0,0,,What could that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.09,0:24:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well there might be several acts that someone possesses, however, if money is made out of one signature act,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.46,0:24:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then you really need to have perfect knowledge of that specific act,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.10,0:24:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise it is not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.57,0:24:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.87,0:24:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for example Degawa-san the comedian
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.14,0:24:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,has an act called "the nose crayfish".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:24:58.81,Hamada,,0,0,0,,If that's the case then do you know the shishimai (lion dance) perfectly?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.81,0:25:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that is obvious Hamada-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.81,0:25:02.61,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Bringing it up regularly...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.35,0:25:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so obvious...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.61,0:25:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I really feel obliged towards it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.65,0:25:07.25,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Since when does this tradition exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.58,0:25:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.25,0:25:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a japanese thing to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.82,0:25:09.89,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Yeah, who started doing it...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.89,0:25:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it from Chinatown?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.45,0:25:12.22,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Who started doing it first?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.22,0:25:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say it at once like that then I can't answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.13,0:25:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I do have the answer but if I am told suddenly like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.43,0:25:18.83,Hamada,,0,0,0,,WHY??
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.13,0:25:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I panicked. I really panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.97,0:25:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I will answer only one question.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.54,0:25:25.94,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Your signature act...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.90,0:25:25.94,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Only one?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.94,0:25:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The question from Harry-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.24,0:25:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with, please tell us if it's a japanese thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.67,0:25:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.54,0:25:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that it has been brought from China.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.52,0:25:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists in China too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.78,0:25:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So how long ago did it come to Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.58,0:25:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean how many years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.29,0:25:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well yeah historically.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.35,0:25:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you gain anything from knowing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.36,0:25:48.23,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Well it's about this theory now...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.23,0:25:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Read the title!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.63,0:25:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.83,0:25:57.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,You are not considered a professional unless you have a perfect knowledge about your signature act.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.14,0:26:00.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,So this time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.17,0:26:02.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,we have invited comedians who
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.34,0:26:05.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,rely on either props or phrases as their signature act.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.41,0:26:10.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To prevent complications, we invited them over for a fake project.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.95,0:26:15.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We then ask them ten questions regarding their signature acts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.39,0:26:18.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If all questions are answered correctly the theory is confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.22,0:26:19.36,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.36,0:26:21.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The first contestant is..
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.43,0:26:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.43,0:26:26.26,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Nagano-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.73,0:26:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to be h...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.57,0:26:31.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Comedian Nagano.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.87,0:26:33.54,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,What was his thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.54,0:26:34.97,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Right, it was Rassen...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.97,0:26:34.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When you think about this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.07,0:26:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I simply....
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.57,0:26:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,LIKE RASSEN!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.68,0:26:43.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A repeated calling of Rassen (a painter) during his act.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.78,0:26:47.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Does he have an understanding about Rassen?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.82,0:26:47.62,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He's says it alot too
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.22,0:26:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nagano-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.45,0:26:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you like Rassen right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.45,0:26:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.85,0:26:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.12,0:26:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I LOVE HIM!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.19,0:26:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I LIKE RASSEN!!!!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.99,0:26:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,...and with this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.56,0:27:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Rassen quiz!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.16,0:27:01.57,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This will be entertaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.57,0:27:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.50,0:27:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see the first question
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.57,0:27:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take a look at this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.57,0:27:06.94,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Well he was caught by surprise so...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.14,0:27:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Which of these paintings is made by Rassen?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.71,0:27:14.24,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's difficult!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.34,0:27:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please answer with A, B or C.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.58,0:27:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one is rassen
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.71,0:27:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I got this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.48,0:27:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Nagano-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.79,0:27:23.55,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's it right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.82,0:27:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply because
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.46,0:27:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have seen this painting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.52,0:27:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.66,0:27:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you own any of Rassen's paintings?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.40,0:27:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought some, yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.83,0:27:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was made to buy.. I bou... yes I have bought
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.83,0:27:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have bought, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.80,0:27:41.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,During a show he purchased a 620.000 yen painting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.57,0:27:44.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,, He got the correct answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.78,0:27:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.88,0:27:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,continuing the Rassen quiz, here is the next question:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.75,0:27:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is Rassen?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.68,0:27:53.98,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Eee, is he gonna know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.98,0:27:55.12,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He knows this doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.12,0:27:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow....
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.15,0:27:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very easy for me
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.75,0:28:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year I actually met Rassen
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.59,0:28:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.33,0:28:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Naganosan? B!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.59,0:28:05.00,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He actually knows this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.73,0:28:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you choose B?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.83,0:28:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I met him!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.20,0:28:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.67,0:28:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,See!?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.77,0:28:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.84,0:28:21.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In this case, he met with Rassen during work, so he got the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.84,0:28:21.91,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Well he said he met him
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.91,0:28:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the next question:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.78,0:28:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What thing related to Rassen does NOT exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.49,0:28:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A: An amusement park attraction, Ocean Rassen The Ride
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.42,0:28:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,B: A pachinko place, CR Rassen World.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.93,0:28:39.10,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.66,0:28:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,C: A game software, Rassen Art Collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.80,0:28:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh, two exist? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.00,0:28:45.77,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Ah so the two exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.80,0:28:43.87,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's starting to get a bit difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.00,0:28:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The two really exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.77,0:28:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So two are real..
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.01,0:28:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Naganosan?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.14,0:28:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the amusement park attraction doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.35,0:28:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No I don't think it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.98,0:28:57.15,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It does sound real though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.35,0:28:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You are correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.18,0:29:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeeesss!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.15,0:29:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The pachinko place "CR Rassen World" opened in 2006.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.99,0:29:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And who played there...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.99,0:29:09.73,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I don't know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.73,0:29:10.79,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Who knows that!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.46,0:29:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The first game software of the Rassen Art collection is the digital jigsaw puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.57,0:29:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.07,0:29:19.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Somehow this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.40,0:29:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"I LIKE RASSEN!!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.74,0:29:24.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,whether that's true or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.67,0:29:28.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he is naturally very strong in the Rassen quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.78,0:29:27.84,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Amazing !
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.61,0:29:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's roll to the next question.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.78,0:29:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Where was Rassen born?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.68,0:29:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A: Hawaii
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.75,0:29:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,B: California
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.75,0:29:38.12,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,, ...It is right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.92,0:29:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,C: Australia
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.83,0:29:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nagano-san
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.36,0:29:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hawaii!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.90,0:29:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think for Rassen...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.03,0:29:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of the paintings
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.27,0:29:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are inspired by sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.34,0:29:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nagano-san
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.17,0:29:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, it's the wrong answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.81,0:30:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The correct answer is B: California
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.75,0:30:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately it was a miss and therefore you will receive a punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.28,0:30:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,HEY NAGANOOOO!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.20,0:30:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You son of a bitch, you like Rassen right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.96,0:30:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.98,0:30:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.35,0:30:17.13,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Typical Aja Kong...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.43,0:30:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You like Rassen?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.31,0:30:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,WHAT IS THIS??
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.57,0:30:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this you're supposed to like Rassen!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.44,0:30:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm seriously scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.77,0:30:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Say it properly that you like Rassen!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.00,0:30:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I LIKE RASSEN!!!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.95,0:30:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.52,0:30:36.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately Nagano failed on the fourth question.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.34,0:30:41.42,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,, But I think he really tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.34,0:30:40.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the next  challenger is...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.41,0:30:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.93,0:30:50.49,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Suddenly his face changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.56,0:30:48.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Gorgeous!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.87,0:30:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Mada tasukaru, ma tasukaru, ma tasukaru (We'll be saved, we'll be saved)!!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.08,0:30:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Madagasukaru (Madagascar)!!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.84,0:30:56.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The one who everyday points at that island...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.26,0:31:01.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Madagascar, but how much does he really know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.61,0:31:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You really picked a good one here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.48,0:31:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorgeous you are always mentioning
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.02,0:31:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a country-island on the African coast
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.88,0:31:13.40,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's how it came!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.59,0:31:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,MADAGASCAR!!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.74,0:31:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.80,0:31:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about it naturally- Madagascar quiz!!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.82,0:31:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a good knowledge of Madagascar?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.56,0:31:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well yes I make sure to point at it correctly everytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.58,0:31:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first question is:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.22,0:31:31.30,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Well at least he knows where it is located.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.27,0:31:38.47,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He should be able to answer this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.72,0:31:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Which of these is Madagascar?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.12,0:31:42.74,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He points at it so he should know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can answer this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.48,0:31:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorgeous-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.93,0:31:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I even looked and pointed at it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.92,0:31:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately it is incorrect!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.03,0:31:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're joking! You're joking
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.60,0:31:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A is...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.76,0:31:56.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's B...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.88,0:31:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Taiwan
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.47,0:31:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.56,0:32:04.45,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This was not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.00,0:32:03.76,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Gorgeous are you serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.94,0:32:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please check with your own eyes the shape of it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.93,0:32:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,THIIIIIIIS...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.29,0:32:16.80,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Their make up matches
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.56,0:32:14.00,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Even the first one was difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.12,0:32:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is Madagascar! Oh you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.23,0:32:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,OI GORGEOUS!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.34,0:32:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,WHAT'S THIS!?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.84,0:32:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,MADAGASCAR!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.45,0:32:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the hell don't you know. Find it on the first try your idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.36,0:32:24.56,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Her voice is loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.58,0:32:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,GET IT RIGHT!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.01,0:32:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.64,0:32:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at it a lot don't ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.92,0:32:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologise to Madagascar!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.10,0:32:34.03,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Let him do his thing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.79,0:32:37.53,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.73,0:32:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry...Saipan! THIIIIIIS....
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.02,0:32:36.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the third challenger is...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.68,0:32:40.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mao's collar quiz with Hattori Yukio (historian).
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.62,0:32:42.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,...but not this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.69,0:32:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,HEYYYYYYY!!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.85,0:32:46.55,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.94,0:32:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Hattori sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.05,0:32:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Aja Kong please take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.76,0:32:57.33,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Aa, that's what it means!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.02,0:32:59.40,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,She got lured...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.70,0:33:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is?...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.70,0:33:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,AJA KONG!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.12,0:33:07.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When you think of Aja you think of a tin drum
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.80,0:33:10.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When you think of a tin drum you think of Aja
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.36,0:33:19.02,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,There's no way she knows anything about it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.97,0:33:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I naturally know about it- the ittokan(Tin drum) quiz!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.82,0:33:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have you wrestled with the ittokan?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.99,0:33:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Around 25-26 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.26,0:33:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All this time together.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.51,0:33:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To you the ittokan is a very valuable signature item right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.87,0:33:30.29,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's kinda like me and the shishimai...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.88,0:33:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah of course it's something more than a signature item.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.75,0:33:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my best partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.18,0:33:37.36,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Her feelings for the ittokan are like me and the shishimai...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.44,0:33:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.19,0:33:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the official name of the ittokan?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.31,0:33:49.75,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,So that's what it means
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.78,0:33:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A: 16-litre drum
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.99,0:33:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,B: 18-litre drum, C:20-litre drum
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.84,0:33:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Kong-san please.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.60,0:33:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,B
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.13,0:33:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,18-litre drum.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.40,0:33:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because itto (volume unit)...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.40,0:33:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is 18 litres right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.97,0:34:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.54,0:34:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.20,0:34:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I at least know the meaning of itto!!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.77,0:34:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the next question:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.39,0:34:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the uses of the ittokan, which is the most common?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.73,0:34:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A: paint
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.77,0:34:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,B: food oil
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.15,0:34:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,C: soy sauce
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.99,0:34:29.61,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.91,0:34:18.72,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.83,0:34:21.93,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I thought it was soy...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.21,0:34:22.20,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Isn't it B?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.49,0:34:25.73,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Is it okay to put soy sauce in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.60,0:34:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are so many uses...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.05,0:34:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well to me soy sauce is the most useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.37,0:34:32.95,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It wasn't oil..
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.40,0:34:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's oil it will be sticky inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.52,0:34:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the juniors it will be difficult to remove.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.42,0:34:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Kongsan?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.29,0:34:36.61,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,She's really thinking about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.63,0:34:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is probably A: paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.40,0:34:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days it might have been soy sauce,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.32,0:34:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but lately it's not very common, before I would go to soba restaurants to get soy drums,, however
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.25,0:34:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,lately soba restaurants are not using soy drums.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.66,0:34:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the supply is very limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.88,0:34:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.08,0:34:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The correct answer is B: food oil
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.48,0:34:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oil huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.14,0:34:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But oil is not going away even if you wash it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.24,0:35:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't use the oil ones
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.70,0:35:02.73,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's not a question whether it's easy to clean..
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.08,0:35:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no clue about the ittokan do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.83,0:35:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do ya think you're talking to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.56,0:35:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be lectured about the drum by someone who has never used it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.64,0:35:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, even though she has no perfect knowledge of the drum,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.66,0:35:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Aja's feelings towards it were certainly communicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.70,0:35:26.37,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Everyone failed didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.37,0:35:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Nagano got three questions right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.11,0:35:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However we could also have answered the first and second questions...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.24,0:35:37.40,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Lately, you've consistently been bad man..
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.40,0:35:39.65,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It's true, if you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.15,0:35:41.92,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Since you came out it's like...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.92,0:35:46.79,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You don't even confirm your theories and still go "thanks for the hard work"...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.79,0:35:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, am I being scolded right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.40,0:35:50.43,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Will you keep appearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.84,0:35:53.92,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,How about you take the night bus?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.90,0:35:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, after 24 years in the industry, will I start taking the night bus?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.70,0:36:02.72,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Do you take the green car (first class train wagon)?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.72,0:36:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I have had the opportunity to be in a green car...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.38,0:36:09.50,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Well this appearance is not worth the green car...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.91,0:36:12.42,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You can take "kodama" (plain wagon)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.45,0:36:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Still better than the bus!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.65,0:36:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Tamura Kenji, the person doing that is Moriwaki Kenji(comedian).
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.49,0:36:16.65,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Much better than bus anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.64,0:36:21.99,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,There you go trash talking about others too...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.98,0:36:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,NO NO It's true! Moriwaki Kenji
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.24,0:36:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,gets on the green car but pays the ticket back and gets on the kodama!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.26,0:36:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am telling the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.69,0:36:39.78,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Here comes the next presenter, welcome!!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.71,0:36:50.52,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It's Tanaka from the Ungirls!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.52,0:36:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.95,0:36:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...this time I thought I will present a theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.37,0:36:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The theory this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.99,0:37:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...seriously what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.11,0:37:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you looking at me all the time!?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.72,0:37:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought of you as a mate!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.10,0:37:08.97,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,As a mate right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.95,0:37:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He is one right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.97,0:37:12.27,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Feels like you guys are plants that live in the same tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.27,0:37:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I am doing this for a long time so cut me some slack!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.80,0:37:20.04,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Actually, you sort of feel like the same food as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.04,0:37:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,About the theory, in old times
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.28,0:37:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a game called "Moero! professional baseball", do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.02,0:37:27.16,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Nintendo?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.21,0:37:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.16,0:37:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you talk about this game, what comes up is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.40,0:37:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that the foreign players' strength settings are so high
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.85,0:37:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that even if they bunt, it ends up being a homerun.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.81,0:37:42.96,Hamada,,0,0,0,,If you hit the ball nicely...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.66,0:37:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.95,0:37:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So this time I brought this:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.05,0:37:51.92,Hamada,,0,0,0,,The theory that if you bunt a ball with a speed of 300 km/h you will still get a home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.77,0:37:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.39,0:37:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't be possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.82,0:37:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.81,0:37:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be able to increase height.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.36,0:38:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It will just go straight and will not reach the seats...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.55,0:38:03.81,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It will not achieve an arched course...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.81,0:38:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is OK, because
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.89,0:38:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you think that if you don't swing upwards you won't get a homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.93,0:38:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but truth is if you hit it horizontally,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.51,0:38:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if the hit is good it will go flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.09,0:38:17.23,Hamada,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.23,0:38:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if it's just..
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.72,0:38:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hit right above the center the angle can be certainly confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.24,0:38:28.37,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,What a creepy way of explaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.65,0:38:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unfair!!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.95,0:38:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's OK we understood you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.56,0:38:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so then it becomes so!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.28,0:38:41.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If a ball comes from a pitching machine at 300 km/h, then a homerun will be achieved even with a bunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.52,0:38:46.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The legendary 1980's Nintendo game
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.25,0:38:46.63,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I don't quite know about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.84,0:38:47.87,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I wasn't even born then.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.63,0:38:50.31,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,You're not born yet
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.26,0:38:48.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Moero! professional baseball"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.68,0:38:51.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the bunt homerun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.12,0:38:57.54,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This was a bunt just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.54,0:39:00.78,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It went over 130 metres!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.09,0:39:01.84,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This was a success just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.31,0:39:03.32,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The games in the 80's man...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.99,0:39:05.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, making this bunt homerun a reality
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.57,0:39:09.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is this machine with a pitching speed of 300 km/h.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.64,0:39:15.92,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's scary!!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.85,0:39:18.29,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I get goosebumps
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.84,0:39:19.57,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Right right, he appeared before.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.30,0:39:21.84,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Last time was not successful but...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.26,0:39:22.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Previously, the challenge taken by ex-professional baseball player Yamasaki Takeshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.65,0:39:28.14,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is very scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.29,0:39:29.36,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,You can't even see the ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.79,0:39:31.29,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's how you'd end up
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.44,0:39:36.24,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,There's nothing but laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.33,0:39:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see it. It went BAM!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.98,0:39:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and with all the smoke...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.56,0:39:42.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.81,0:39:46.80,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Isn't it amazing, scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.69,0:39:46.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If this is the pitching speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.09,0:39:50.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,there is no chance of a bunt home run.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.42,0:39:52.10,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,This is a nice theory
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.88,0:39:54.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In order to back this experiment scientifically,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.57,0:40:00.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,we asked the science fiction investigator Yanagita Rikao.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.01,0:40:00.24,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's an amazing name.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.03,0:40:00.85,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Fiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.78,0:40:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is whether it's possible to achieve a bunt homerun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.23,0:40:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Given that the bat is securely fixed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.90,0:40:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the ball could fly 122 metres according to the calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.27,0:40:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When the bat is fixed, then the balls speed after impact
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.21,0:40:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,equals the ball's initial speed times the ball's elasticity coefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.37,0:40:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case the ball's resistance is approximately 0.42.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.04,0:40:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So 300 times 0.42 equals 126 km as the ball's speed after impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.84,0:40:37.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If the ball has a speed of 126 km, then it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.39,0:40:42.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,can result in a 122 metre homerun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.63,0:40:46.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And on the day of the experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.57,0:40:50.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just like Rikao sensei suggested,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.43,0:40:54.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A metal base was fixated on the batter's box.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.96,0:40:56.28,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I hope this works.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.12,0:40:59.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And this time, prepared exclusively for the show,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.13,0:41:03.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is this 300km/h pitching machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.80,0:41:09.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Rikao sensei is also on the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.07,0:41:12.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And with that, the preparations are completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.65,0:41:15.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Will it be possible to achieve a bunt homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.44,0:41:19.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with this 300km /h pitching machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.11,0:41:22.88,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Why that face!?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.58,0:41:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good face.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.37,0:41:26.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Will it be possible to achieve a bunt homerun
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.70,0:41:30.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with this 300km /h pitching machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.94,0:41:34.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,First of, a wooden bat was fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.41,0:41:37.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And a memorable first try!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.37,0:41:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.58,0:41:50.14,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,What came off? Ah, the arm...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.26,0:41:53.44,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It came off on the first try...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.90,0:41:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Something seems to have gotten in...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.10,0:41:56.41,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Not even close...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.41,0:41:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a dead ball right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:02.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The ball was pitched
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.91,0:42:02.76,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That was it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.35,0:42:07.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Going straight towards Hamada's armpit, it just ripped the arm off.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.21,0:42:11.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the sight of this, the expectations of a homerun are rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.64,0:42:17.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The ball's speed during this pitch was 304 km/h.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.48,0:42:21.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After adjusting the ball's course, the experiment continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.61,0:42:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.83,0:42:28.43,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,On the second try?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.98,0:42:41.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Gaining a great height, the ball passes the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.89,0:42:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.26,0:42:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it is possible after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.56,0:42:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We need another 5 millimetres.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.64,0:42:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,5 millimetres yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.16,0:42:56.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, the next pitch...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.52,0:42:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.56,0:43:04.19,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It broke!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.93,0:43:08.22,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It came off..
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.02,0:43:08.22,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It broke!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.98,0:43:12.11,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's like the wig came off...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.70,0:43:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It broke off!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.59,0:43:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It did...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.98,0:43:21.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Not tolerating the ball's massive speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.55,0:43:24.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the bat just broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.43,0:43:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an uncommon way of breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.03,0:43:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.53,0:43:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally it grazes through
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.40,0:43:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and cuts the wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.74,0:43:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But this just snapped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.08,0:43:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It got ripped instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.03,0:43:45.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The bat may have snapped, but the bunt was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.77,0:43:50.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so this time a metal bat was prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.40,0:43:52.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the experiment resumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.04,0:43:58.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With an unbreakable metal bat, a bunt homerun should be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.15,0:44:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.12,0:44:15.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It hit a good spot
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.92,0:44:19.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Where is the ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.43,0:44:29.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It reached second base...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.20,0:44:33.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In case Rikao sensei miss calculated...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.85,0:44:36.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,we examined the pitch using slow motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.10,0:44:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It bent so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.40,0:44:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It does yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.58,0:44:48.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The bat just warps like rubber under the ball's high speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.67,0:44:52.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and it just absorbed its force.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.78,0:44:58.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,, With the unexpected turn of events, Rikao sensei checks his calculations...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.80,0:44:58.59,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He looks very cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.42,0:44:56.80,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Quit him already...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.30,0:45:01.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In order to make the impossible possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.87,0:45:07.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,his answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.82,0:45:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If we use tennis balls
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.07,0:45:07.82,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,The answer is!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.28,0:45:14.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Use tennis balls!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.25,0:45:15.04,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It started getting weird this theory!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.89,0:45:19.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Will a bunt homerun be accomplished with tennis balls?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.36,0:45:43.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In order to achieve homerun, the answer that Rikao sensei gave is...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.63,0:45:45.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Tennis balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.51,0:45:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You considered the tennis ball's heaviness?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.64,0:45:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.68,0:45:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to a baseball, the tennis ball has a greater elasticity coefficient,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.45,0:45:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so that will make the ball fly easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.08,0:45:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think it's possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.72,0:45:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.67,0:46:04.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Moreover, to achieve bunt homerun, the pitching machine was moved closer to the batter,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.19,0:46:08.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the tennis balls' proneness to slow down was covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.20,0:46:14.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,According to calculations, this will achieve a pitching distance 3 times higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.03,0:46:18.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At last, will that result in the bunt homerun we have been dreaming?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.80,0:46:23.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The time of the fateful result is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.13,0:46:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.99,0:46:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.39,0:46:39.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A pitch that was completely covered on camera
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.07,0:46:44.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Has science accomplished a bunt homerun?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.34,0:46:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.61,0:46:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.03,0:46:53.69,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's not flying at all
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.58,0:46:55.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A second base...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.68,0:47:01.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And to conclude, a bunt homerun is only a game thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.00,0:47:04.19,Hamada,,0,0,0,,TANAKA!!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.76,0:47:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologise!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.65,0:47:06.86,Hamada,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.45,0:47:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It concluded so suddenly..
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.13,0:47:08.51,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.59,0:47:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Emm what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.46,0:47:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I am very sorry, everything i said before was gibberish...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.09,0:47:17.60,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,This V (sounds B in Japanese), didn't even result in a band...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.60,0:47:19.84,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I don't like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.84,0:47:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't help this!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.08,0:47:24.20,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,That doll was mistreated as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.20,0:47:27.52,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I really felt bad for my partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.27,0:47:30.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Next week
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.48,0:47:34.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The theory that the funny skits in pretty girls' phone are not funny at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.28,0:47:37.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The name of this ingredient is that we find in fukujinzuke (pickles),
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.23,0:47:39.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is not known by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.80,0:47:44.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Also, is you reverse a prank multiple times, you end up losing confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.85,0:47:50.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And finally, we investigate the theory of the worst speaker in pro-wrestling, Maeda Akira.
